Thanks @rshin and @wesm! Those are good points. And I agree it'd be nice to find a way to avoid the `std::list`.

@swang, I guess the question is should we try to convert from C to C++ gradually? Or should we just go ahead and convert the whole local scheduler right now (e.g., switch to using classes, no calls to `new`/`delete` etc.

